{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s32_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6470c8",
"children":[
"For patients with acute liver failure, choose:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b60404",
"children":[
"immediate contact with liver transplantation center"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f96e76",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"N"
]
},
"-acetylcysteine for confirmed or suspected acetaminophen poisoning"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"05013b",
"children":[
"lactulose for any degree of encephalopathy"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"071f73",
"children":[
"Head CT should be performed in patients with acute liver failure and altered mental status to rule out cerebral edema or intracranial hemorrhage."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s32_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e9e220",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 24-year-old man has a 1-week history of nausea, jaundice, fatigue, and recent confusion. The ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"international normalized ratio",
"children":[
"INR"
]
},
" is 2.3, serum AST is 940 U/L, and total bilirubin is 12.6 mg/dL. ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hepatitis B surface antigen",
"children":[
"HBsAg"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"anti-HAV IgM antibodies to hepatitis A virus",
"children":[
"IgM"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"antibodies to hepatitis B core antigen",
"children":[
"anti-HBc"
]
},
" are both positive."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"abe88a",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose acute liver failure secondary to acute HBV infection. For management, contact liver transplantation center."
]
}
]
}
]
},
